  "prompt": "How do you know who viewed you video on Instagram?",
  "response": "As of now, Instagram does not provide a feature that allows users to see exactly who viewed their regular video posts (as opposed to Stories). Instagram Stories do have a view count feature that shows you how many people have viewed your Story and, if your account is public or you allow it in private settings, you can see the usernames of those who have viewed it.\n\nBut for regular video posts (posted directly to your Instagram feed), you can only see the total number of likes, comments, and views (for videos longer than one second). You cannot see the identities of the individual viewers.\n\nHere is how to view the view count on a video post:\n\n1. Open the Instagram app and go to the video post you are interested in.\n2. Below the video, you will see the number of views the video has received, displayed on the left side of the like count.\n3. Tap on the view count to see the total number of views, but not the specific usernames of the viewers.\n\nIf you come across any third-party apps or services claiming to provide detailed viewer information for Instagram video posts, be cautious. These apps are not authorized by Instagram, and using them may violate Instagram's terms of service, pose privacy risks, or potentially compromise your account security.\n\nIf Instagram updates its features to allow viewing of who has watched video posts, the method to access this information would be through the official app, and users would be informed about the new feature through Instagram's official channels. Always make sure to follow Instagram\u2019s guidelines and use the official app for any activity related to your account.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
